%N A254763 One half of the fundamental positive solution y = y2(n) of the second class of the Pell equation x^2 - 2*y^2 = A007519(n), n>=1 (primes congruent to 1 mod 8).
%C A254763 The corresponding fundamental solution x2(n) of this second class of positive solutions is given in A254762(n).
%C A254763 See the comments and the Nagell reference in A254760.
%F A254763 A254762(n)^2 - 2*(2*a(n))^2 = A007519(n) gives the second smallest positive (proper) solution of this (generalized) Pell equation.
%F A254763 a(n) = A254760(n) - 3*A254761(n), n >= 1.
%e A254763 n = 2: 13^2 - 2*(2*4)^2 = 169 - 128 = 41.
%e A254763 The smallest positive solution is (x1(2), y1(2)) = (7, 2) from (A254760(2), 2*A254761(2)).
%e A254763 See also A254762.
%e A254763 a(4) = 11 - 3*2 = 5.
